HEADWORD: Fallowness
<hw>Fal"low*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A well or opening, through the
successive floors of a warehouse or manufactory, through which goods are
raised or lowered.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
